buyTokens(uint256).details: Allows users to purchase tokens during the ICO.

params._etherAmount: The amount in wei to spend on token purchase.

calculateTokenAmount(uint256).details: Calculates the token amount based on the ether amount.

params._etherAmount: The amount in wei sent for the purchase.

returns._0: The number of tokens that can be purchased.

endICO().details: Ends the ICO and transfers any remaining tokens to the owner.

params._discountRate: The initial discount rate for the ICO in basis points (0-10000).
params._endTime: The end time of the ICO.
params._maxPurchase: The maximum purchase amount in wei.
params._minPurchase: The minimum purchase amount in wei.
params._startTime: The start time of the ICO.
params._tokenContract: The address of the ERC20 token contract.
params._tokenPrice: The base price of one token in wei.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setDiscountRate(uint256).details: Sets the discount rate for the ICO.

params._newDiscountRate: The new discount rate in basis points (0-10000).

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
